                    <span>People say this book is no good just because it's too "confusing."  Well, just because you don't understand it, doesn't mean that the book is bad.  Dumbing down ideas doesn't make a book better.  I understood this book quite well.  I also love this Mr. Bradbury's imagination.  If you liked this book, you should also read Dandolion Wine, another book by this great author.  If you don't like this book because it's too confusing, just don't read it.  It is a great book and seeing all those "1 star" reviews for being confusing is a real pitty.</span>
                  
